race.description: Civicipn Valuers Country Boosted Maiden Plate
race.comment: GAIL JEANETTE (9) led at Wellington first-up and was back on track beaten a nose as favourite. Has raced and Group and Stakes level and has plenty to give. Maps well and is the one to beat. IMASTATEMENT (7) resumed in the same race beaten 1.3L. Draws inside and she has more to offer. She will get every chance to bridge the gap. JUST JOAN (8) peaks and is going well enough to make the finish. Missed a whisker at Muswellbrook two back, and the 2kg claim is handy. Can take a sit and come late. COMOBELLA (6) has been off the scene for a long while but has trialled well at Warren. Disappointed at Orange on debut over the short course, and this looks a better starting point. Has a handy 2kg claim and deserves to be kept onside.
